'''紅色天鵝絨蛋糕'''（{{lang-en|Red velvet cake}}）或稱'''紅絲絨蛋糕'''，為一種[[栗色|深紅色]]或[[咖啡色|咖啡色]]的[[巧克力蛋糕|巧克力蛋糕]]，在[[美國南部|美國南部]]最普遍。它通常用在聖誕節或情人節，材料包括麵粉、奶油、食糖、酪漿、可可粉（或奶油芝士）、糖霜、甜菜根和食用紅色色素<ref>{{cite web|last1=Crocker|first1=Betty|title=Red Velvet Cake|url=http://www.bettycrocker.com/how-to/tipslibrary/baking-tips/red-velvet-cake|website=bettycrocker.com|publisher=General Mills|accessdate=2017-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://qz.com/344195/the-rediscovery-of-red-velvet-has-gone-way-too-far/ |title=The rediscovery of red velvet has gone way too far |year=2015 |website=Quartz |access-date=2016-12-04}}</ref>。

== 歷史 ==
[[File:Red_velvet_cupcake.jpg|thumb]]
1972年{{link-en|詹姆士·比爾德|James Beard}}的參考文獻美式烹飪，描述了三種红色天鵝絨蛋糕，其中起酥油、奶油和[[植物油|植物油]]的量不同<ref>{{cite book | last = Beard | first = James | title = James Beard's American Cookery | url = https://archive.org/details/jamesbeardsameri00bear | publisher = Little, Brown | year = 1972 | location = Boston }}</ref>。全部使用紅色食物，但酸性醋和酪漿的反應顯示了可可粉中的紅色[[花青素|花青素]]，並保持了蛋糕的潤澤、明亮和蓬鬆。其天然色調可能是名稱由來，和惡魔蛋糕類似<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.njbbt.org/ripoff1161.htm | title = It's All Mixed Up! The History and True Facts About Baking Devil's Food Cake | accessdate = 2004-10-10 | last = Scott | first = Suzanne | date = 2003-06-07 | publisher = New Jersey Baker's Board of Trade | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20040805042002/http://www.njbbt.org/ripoff1161.htm | archivedate = 2004-08-05 }}</ref>；現在的巧克力會以荷蘭的技術防止花青素色變<ref>{{Cite web|title = Red Velvet Cake|url = http://bigbaketheory.com/2012/01/13/red-velvet-cake/|website = The Big Bake Theory|accessdate = 2016-01-02}}</ref><ref name=Fabricant>{{cite news|last=Fabricant|first=Florence|title=So Naughty, So Nice|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/14/dining/14velv.html?pagewanted=all|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2007-02-14|accessdate=2012-08-22}}</ref>。

當[[第二次世界大战|第二次世界大战]]期間食物[[配給制|配給制]]時，麵包師使用煮熟的甜菜汁來增加其蛋糕的顏色。甜菜頭被發現在一些紅色天鵝絨蛋糕食譜，在那裡也用於保持水分。一家[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]]的{{link-en|Adams Extract|Adams Extract}}公司，被譽為在[[大萧条|大萧条]]時期將紅色天鵝絨蛋糕帶到美國各地的年代。通過出售紅色食品著色劑成為第一個銷售紅色食品的公司並使用銷售點海報和撕下食譜卡<ref>{{cite web|last=Parks |first=Stella |title=The Unknown History of Red Velvet Cake |publisher=Gilttaste.com |date=2011-10-02 |accessdate=2012-11-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/stories/sectionfront/life/red-velvet-the-lady-gaga-of-cakes-wears-well-during-the-holidays-224246/ |title=Red Velvet, the 'Lady Gaga' of cakes, wears well during the holidays |publisher=Post-gazette.com |date=2011-12-15 |accessdate=2012-11-08}}</ref>。這個蛋糕及其原始食譜從美國[[紐約華爾道夫酒店|紐約華爾道夫酒店]]聞名，這被稱為華爾道夫─阿斯托里亞蛋糕。然而，它被廣泛認為是個{{link-en|南美菜|Cuisine of the Southern United States}}<ref name=Fabricant/>；傳統上，紅色天鵝絨蛋糕用法式[[奶油炒麵糊|奶油炒麵糊]]（也叫做[[冰雹|冰雹]]），這非常輕鬆但準備耗時，[[奶油芝士|奶油芝士]]和奶油糖霜是人氣增加的主因<ref name="Martha">{{cite web |url=http://www.marthastewart.com/353779/cream-cheese-frosting-red-velvet-cake |author=Martha Stewart |title=
Cream Cheese Frosting for Red Velvet Cake |accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref><ref name="nyt">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/14/dining/red-velvet-cake-from-gimmick-to-american-classic.html?_r=0 |author=Kim Severson |title=Red Velvet Cake: A Classic, Not a Gimmick |accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref>。

在[[加拿大|加拿大]]，蛋糕是1940至1950年代在[[伊頓公司|伊頓公司]]餐廳和麵包店的知名甜點。作為伊頓獨家推廣，知道食譜的員工宣誓就要沉默，許多人誤認為蛋糕是百貨公司{{link-en|伊頓華|Flora Eaton}}發明的<ref>{{cite book | last = Anderson | first = Carol |author2=Katharine Mallinson | title = Lunch with Lady Eaton: Inside the Dining Rooms of a Nation | year = 2004 | publisher = ECW Press | location = Toronto | isbn = 1-55022-650-9 }}</ref>。

近年來，紅色天鵝絨蛋糕和紅絲絨紙杯蛋糕在美國和歐洲許多國家越來越受歡迎。這種蛋糕的普及，一些歸功於1989年的“{{link-en|鋼木蘭|Steel Magnolias}}”，其中包括以[[犰狳科|犰狳]]形式製成的紅色天鵝絨{{link-en|新郎蛋糕|Groom's cake}}，自1996年{{link-en|木蘭麵包店|Magnolia Bakery}}在[[曼哈頓|曼哈頓]]開業以來，像南美菜的餐廳，如[[谭恩美|谭恩美]]1998年於[[哈莱姆区|哈莱姆区]]開業也是如此<ref name=Fabricant /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://nymag.com/listings/restaurant/amy-ruths-home-style-southern-cuisine/|title=Amy Ruth's Home-Style Southern Cuisine|publisher=New York magazine|accessdate=2014-03-27}}</ref>；2000年，{{link-en|掠奪蛋糕人|Cake Man Raven}}在[[布鲁克林区|布鲁克林区]]開了第一個專門用於蛋糕的麵包店<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/brooklyn/cake-man-raven-red-velvet-cake-flight-bigger-better-article-1.1209029|title=Cake Man Raven has flown the coop — no more red velvet cake in Fort Greene|publisher=NY Daily News|date=2012-11-28}}</ref>。

